      "outcome": "The secular magistrate receives the petition and schedules a preliminary hearing for the next judicial session. While no ruling is issued, the magistrate's clerk formally docket the case — meaning the Secular Merchants' Coalition now has a pending legal action on record. This procedural milestone gives the Coalition de facto standing: any Council attempt to excommunicate Coalition members before the hearing could be challenged as contempt of pending proceedings. The Council is forced to pause its excommunication threats, buying the Coalition breathing room. Meanwhile, the Wardens use the filing as propaganda — distributing copies of the docket receipt to market operators as proof that \"the secular courts recognize our legitimacy.\" Three additional market operators sign the Coalition charter, and two wavering gondola operators who had defected to the Families' subsidized program quietly return, calculating that legal protection is worth more than short-term savings. The Families take note: if the Coalition gains formal guild status, the Wardens could challenge their permanent routing charter in the same court.",
