      "action": "Deploy Warden garrison to enforce mandatory cargo inspections on all gondola freight originating from the Lantern-Lit Gondola Pier and transiting through Tower Bridge Concourse. The inspections, justified under \"Coalition security protocols,\" target the Signal-House Families' subsidized freight program by creating 4-6 hour delays for non-Coalition-permitted cargo. Wardens also establish a \"priority lane\" for Coalition Permit holders, offering expedited passage within 30 minutes. The inspection checkpoint is positioned at the Concourse's narrowest bottleneck, maximizing delay impact.",
      "outcome": "The mandatory inspection regime immediately impacts the Families' subsidized freight program. Of the 23 gondola operators who defected to the Families, 9 return to the Coalition within the first week, calculating that the time-cost of delays outweighs the 40% fee discount. The Families' guaranteed minimum revenue payments to operators now include delay compensation, increasing their subsidy costs by an estimated 25%. However, the Families respond by rerouting some bulk cargo through longer canal paths to avoid the Concourse bottleneck entirely, reducing Warden tariff collection on those shipments to zero. The Wardens' total tariff revenue stabilizes but does not recover to pre-subsidy levels. Market operators increasingly view the Concourse as a contested chokepoint rather than a neutral commercial hub. The Families dispatch a formal protest to the secular magistrate, accusing the Wardens of anti-competitive gatekeeping — the first legal challenge to the Coalition's parallel jurisdiction.",
      "targetLocation": "Tower Bridge Concourse",
      "tagChangeCount": 3,
      "chronicleEntryId": "d7730a8c-eb48-42e8-a3cd-e6e9d1431769"
    }
