      "action": "Withdraw the covert monitoring station from the Silent Spire canal approach and redeploy the signal intelligence detachment to establish a new acoustic surveillance perimeter around the Night Courier Depot, repurposing the captured acoustic fragments to develop counter-jamming protocols for the Depot's message routing systems. The withdrawal is framed publicly as \"respecting the consecration\" while privately the Families redirect their cryptographers to focus on defending the Depot's permanent routing charter against the Wardens' inevitable legal challenge. The Families also dispatch a formal diplomatic communiqué to the Silent Spire Keepers acknowledging the consecration and requesting a neutral meeting to discuss \"mutual signal integrity concerns\" — an attempt to open back-channel dialogue without conceding their technological interests.",
      "outcome": "The covert monitoring station is dismantled within 48 hours, averting the immediate excommunication threat. The signal intelligence detachment relocates to the Night Courier Depot, where they establish acoustic countermeasures calibrated to protect the Depot's telegraph infrastructure from potential Keepers' jamming. The captured acoustic fragments, while obsolete for deciphering the Unspoken Tongue, provide enough data to develop preliminary jamming-resistant signal protocols — a defensive capability the Families lacked before. The diplomatic communiqué to the Keepers receives a terse acknowledgment but no meeting is scheduled; the Keepers remain suspicious but the excommunication threat is defused. The Families' public framing of the withdrawal as \"respecting consecrated waters\" plays well with neutral market operators who view the Council's liturgical authority as legitimate. However, the Wardens interpret the withdrawal as weakness and accelerate their preparations for the seasonal charter review, filing a formal petition to the secular magistrate challenging the Families' permanent routing charter on grounds of \"insufficient security provisions.\"",
      "targetLocation": "Night Courier Depot",
      "tagChangeCount": 3,
      "chronicleEntryId": "f32c93bf-3722-4b8b-b21f-9ac2aec56624"
    }
